# shadcn/ui Usage — MANDATORY

This project uses [shadcn/ui](https://ui.shadcn.com/) for **every single UI element**. This is a hard requirement with **zero exceptions**.

> **ABSOLUTE RULE: No custom UI components. No raw HTML elements. No other UI libraries. shadcn/ui only.**

## Initialization

shadcn/ui is **not yet initialized** in this project. If you need to use it for the first time, run:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest init
```

## Adding Components

Components are installed on demand. To add a component (e.g. `button`):

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add button
```

Installed components live in `src/components/ui/` and are imported from there:

```tsx
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
```

## Rules

- **NEVER** create custom UI components from scratch. Always find the appropriate shadcn/ui component.
- **NEVER** use raw HTML elements (`<button>`, `<input>`, `<div>` as UI containers, `<a>` as buttons, etc.) when a shadcn/ui component exists for that purpose.
- **NEVER** use any other UI library (Radix directly, MUI, Chakra, Headless UI, etc.).
- **ALWAYS** use shadcn/ui components — for buttons, inputs, dialogs, cards, badges, dropdowns, toasts, and every other UI primitive.
- Before using a component, verify it exists in `src/components/ui/`. If it doesn't, install it with `npx shadcn@latest add <component-name>`.
- Do **not** modify the generated files inside `src/components/ui/` directly — extend them via composition in feature components instead.
- Refer to the [shadcn/ui component docs](https://ui.shadcn.com/docs/components) for available components and their APIs.
- This project is in dark mode so make sure there are no dark colored text on dark backgrounds (and vice versa).

## Clerk Authentication UI

All Clerk sign-in and sign-up UI **must** follow these rules:

- **NEVER** use Clerk's default `<SignInButton>` or `<SignUpButton>` rendered as-is. Always wrap them with a shadcn/ui `<Button>` as the child trigger.
- **ALWAYS** use `mode="modal"` on `<SignInButton>` and `<SignUpButton>` so authentication opens in a modal overlay, not a redirect to a separate page.
- The shadcn `<Button>` must be the `asChild` consumer or the direct child of the Clerk button component.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — Clerk modal with shadcn Button
import { SignInButton, SignUpButton } from "@clerk/nextjs";
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";

<SignInButton mode="modal">
  <Button variant="outline">Sign In</Button>
</SignInButton>

<SignUpButton mode="modal">
  <Button>Get Started</Button>
</SignUpButton>

// ❌ BAD — raw Clerk button with no modal, no shadcn
<SignInButton />

// ❌ BAD — custom styled div/anchor acting as button
<SignInButton mode="modal">
  <div className="btn">Sign In</div>
</SignInButton>
```
